Breaking News Man found guilty in 2013 Delray double homicide Dutch eventing draws 60,000 spectators A girl makes her dog jump over an obstacle for horses during the cross-country discipline of the Eventing at the Military Boekelo, eastern Netherlands, Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015. More than 60,000 spectators enjoyed a day of Olympic-standard equestrian competition when they attended the Military Boekelo, one of the biggest sporting events held in the Netherlands. Eventing competition consists of dressage, cross-country and show jumping and competitors were seeking a spot at the Rio Olympics at the picturesque competition held near the city of Enschede.
